```scala
abstract class A {
    type T
}

def f(a: A, t: a.T) { }
```

fails to compile:
```scala
(fragment of hello.scala):5: error: illegal dependent method type
def f(a: A, t: a.T) { }
```


Use case is:
```scala
class PropertyType {
  type ValueType
}

class LengthPropertyType {
  type ValueType = Int
}

def addProperty(propertyType: PropertyType, value: propertyType.ValueType) { ... }
```
